body:
This is caused by LeakCanary tracking removed root views as of version 2.6 : https://square.github.io/leakcanary/changelog/#detecting-root-views-retained-after-viewondetachedfromwindow

You can work around that by filtering which objects can be considered retained: https://square.github.io/leakcanary/changelog/#configuring-retained-object-detection

```
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<resources>
  <bool name="leak_canary_watcher_auto_install">false</bool>
</resources>
```

This removes detection of root view being detached:

```
class DebugExampleApplication : ExampleApplication() {

  override fun onCreate() {
    super.onCreate()

    val watchersToInstall = AppWatcher.appDefaultWatchers(application)
      .filter { it !is RootViewWatcher }

    AppWatcher.manualInstall(
      application = application,
      watchersToInstall = watchersToInstall
    )
  }
}
``` 

This adds it back but can be customized to ignore specific instances:

```
class DebugExampleApplication : ExampleApplication() {

  override fun onCreate() {
    super.onCreate()

    val watchersToInstall = AppWatcher.appDefaultWatchers(application)
      .filter { it !is RootViewWatcher } + RootViewWatcher { watchedObject, description ->
          val  view = watchedObject as View
          if (/* check a property of the root view indicating it's a dialog that comes and goes */) {
            return@RootViewWatcher
          }
          AppWatcher.objectWatcher.expectWeaklyReachable(watchedObject, description)
        }

    AppWatcher.manualInstall(
      application = application,
      watchersToInstall = watchersToInstall
    )
  }
}
```
